---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | SexualHarassmentCalc';
const description = 'Contact SexualHarassmentCalc for corrections, content suggestions, and press inquiries.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p><em>Reviewed by our editorial team. Updated May 2026.</em></p>

  <p>
    Reach the editorial team at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We read every message and
    respond to legitimate inquiries within a few business days.
  </p>

  <h2>What we can help with</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Corrections.</strong> Factual errors, broken statute or case citations, outdated worked examples. Include the page URL and a brief description.</li>
    <li><strong>Content suggestions.</strong> Topics we should cover, a misconception we missed, a state statute that has materially changed.</li>
    <li><strong>Press and republication.</strong> Quoting the site or asking the editorial team to comment on a story.</li>
    <li><strong>Editorial team feedback.</strong> Comments on a specific reviewer&rsquo;s page or on our editorial standards.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we cannot help with</h2>
  <p>
    We do not provide legal advice, evaluate specific harassment situations, refer to attorneys, or intervene with employers.
    If you are trying to figure out whether your situation has a viable claim, contact a licensed employment plaintiff&rsquo;s
    attorney in your state. Many offer free initial consultations on contingency-eligible matters. You can also contact your
    nearest <a href="https://www.eeoc.gov/field-office">EEOC field office</a> or your state&rsquo;s fair-employment agency. Deadlines
    are short; do not wait on us to email you back before reaching out to a lawyer or an agency.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy of correspondence</h2>
  <p>
    Email you send us is read by the editorial team only. We do not share, sell, or republish reader correspondence. See the
    <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for full details on how the site handles data.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
